# Vue 3 Patterns

## Component Structure
- Always use `<script setup lang="ts">` — never Options API, never `defineComponent`
- Order within SFC: `<script setup>` → `<template>` → `<style scoped>`
- One component per file, filename matches component name in PascalCase

## Composition
- Extract reusable logic into composables in `src/composables/use<Name>.ts`
- Composables must start with `use` and return a plain object (not reactive wrapper)
- Prefer `computed` over methods for derived state

## Props & Emits
```vue
// ✅ GOOD
const props = defineProps<{ title: string; count?: number }>()
const emit = defineEmits<{ update: [value: number] }>()

// ❌ BAD
props: { title: String }
```

## Reactivity
- Use `ref` for primitives, `reactive` for objects — be consistent
- Never destructure `reactive` objects directly (loses reactivity)
- Use `toRefs` when you need to destructure a reactive object

## Routing & State
- Use `vue-router` with typed routes — define route names as a const enum
- Use `pinia` for global state — one store per domain, not one giant store

## PWA Specifics
- Register service worker only in production builds
- Handle offline state explicitly — always show the user a meaningful offline UI
